<h1 class="bac"><%=program.Item("title")%></h1>

<div class="expanded">
<% call expandableH2("our_business", true) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">The Global Wealth &amp; Investment Management Operations organization provides support for over 10 million brokerage private wealth management and trust accounts globally , as well as more than 44,000 employee benefit plans with our 4.9 million participants. In total, this represents $1.9 trillion in client assets. Also, the organization provides operational service expertise to hundreds of offices and over 15,000 Financial Advisors conducting business in more than 120 countries around the world.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("overview", false) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">The GWIM Operations Analyst Program is an undergraduate program is designed to give associates the necessary tools, early in their careers, to manage their professional development, realize their potential, and maximize their contributions to Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America.</p>
<p class="bac">GWIM OAP is a Development program that focuses on operational line of business functions within Global Wealth &amp; Investment Management Technology &amp; Operations and provides associates with the opportunity to move through two rotational assignments within various groups of the organization.  GWIM OAP associates participate in a variety of activities designed to foster teamwork, encourage networking, and demonstrate Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America&#39;s vision and culture.</p>
<h3 class="bac nobr">Two 1-year rotational assignments in which potential roles/responsibilities may include:</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li><span class="un">Business Support Lead</span>:  Provides business support to a team; responsibilities include data collection and analysis, project implementation/point of contact, and performance catalyst.</li>
	<li><span class="un">Operations Team Lead</span>:  Directs a small unit or section of internal operations activities; responsibilities focus on the day to day resolution of problems and execution of transactions within specific operations units requiring immediate and frequent involvement with unit activities.</li>
	<li><span class="un">Operations Analyst</span>:  Performs day-to-day analysis, research and resolution of varied problems; administers defined procedures, analysis/report generation, and exception processing.</li>
	<li><span class="un">Operational Risk Specialist</span>: Analyzes existing practices within operational risk management across the company in the areas of data management, data quality, information and reporting; develops solutions to problems identified which yield productivity gains consistent with company goals.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>
<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("qualifications", false) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">Successful candidates will possess and demonstrate the ability to work in a fast paced, empowered environment.  Ideal candidates will have the demonstrated ability to handle multiple, competing priorities; learn new tools/applications quickly; and possess strong interpersonal skills and proficiencies in critical thinking, leadership outside of the classroom, business acumen, and relationship building.</p>
<h3 class="bac nobr">Candidate Profile</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Recent graduate from an accredited school with a bachelor&#39;s degree in one of the following majors: Business Management, Business Administration, Finance, Operations Management, Information Management, Statistics, Economics, or Industrial Engineering</li>
	<li>Willingness to work varied schedules, including swing shift for specific operations positions</li>
	<li>Solid organization skills, excellent planning ability and project management skills</li>
	<li>Ability to communicate effectively in both written and verbal communications</li>
	<li>Sound judgment and the ability to deal with ambiguity and high pressure situations in a changing environment</li>
	<li>High standard of Professionalism</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("training", false) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">The GWIM OAP training curriculum is comprehensive and offers a blend of classroom and web-based training, which complements the hands-on experience that the GWIM Operations associates develop in their rotational assignments.</p>
</div></div>

